Package org.epochx.tools.eval

Interface Summary
Interpreter Interpreters provide a mechanism for executing program source code that is being evolved by a grammar based representation or otherwise.
 

Class Summary
BrainfuckInterpreter A BrainfuckInterpreter provides the facility to execute programs in the esoteric Brainfuck programming language.
EpoxInterpreter An EpoxInterpreter provides the facility to evaluate individual Epox expressions.
GroovyInterpreter A GroovyInterpreter provides the facility to evaluate individual Groovy expressions and execute multi-line Groovy statements.
JavaInterpreter A JavaInterpreter provides the facility to evaluate individual Java expressions and execute multi-line Java statements.
RubyInterpreter A RubyInterpreter provides the facility to evaluate individual Ruby expressions and execute multi-line Ruby statements.
ScriptingInterpreter The ScriptingInterpreter provides a generic interpreter for any language which supports the javax.scripting API (JSR 223).
 

Exception Summary
MalformedProgramException Checked exception that indicates that a program being evaluated, executed or otherwise processed has been found to be incorrectly formed according to the appropriate syntax rules.
